			<ns0:name>eli...@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/112264824292994369940/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">LLVM r174446 changes the opcodes used to modify SP in function prologs/epilogs in case of x32. This has implications for our rewrite pass that should now expect the 32-bit opcodes and not the 64-bit opcodes. This change has to be cherry picked before the next merge or at least taken into account.

